verbose_text: In a multiple sclerosis (MS) model it was shown that TNF-alpha decreased disease severity in myelin oligodendrocyte glycoprotein (MOG)-induced demyelination whereas systemic lupus erthymatosis (SLE) may result from unregulated expression of the TNF-alpha homologue zTNF4 (Blys, BAFF, TALL-1, THANK).
evidence: expression of the TNF-alpha homologue zTNF4
